parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag can cause serious injury or death due to the explosion of the airbag inflator, which can send shrapnel into the passenger compartment.
symptoms: None
as the issue is related to the potential failure of the airbag in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to become stiff or travel to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels stiff or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the brake pedal makes a hissing or squealing noise
the vehicle is difficult to stop
the brake pedal has to be pumped to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Failure to Engage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to engage or slipping can cause the vehicle to jerk or stall, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or slips when shifting gears
the transmission hesitates or fails to engage
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission makes a loud clunking or whining noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body Assembly or Switch Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body assembly or switch can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or loss of control.

the vehicle has a burning smell but no smoke is visible.
